""the me too movement of the bible."" understanding the will of god through the word of god and the me too movement i had great hesitation in writing a book about the me too movement and the bible. in my hesitation
column3: i begin to think that maybe a woman should write this book. in this book
column4: i would be challenged to write¬†about things that most preachers never preach or teach in their bible lessons. the sunday school lessons that are written never deal with the issue of sexual assault. most books that are written in the christian arena never deal with the issues that will be discussed in this book. i am about to write about something that if i came across in a movie
column5: i would turn the movie off because i do not find such matters entertaining even in the world of make-believe movies.

column3: has been named the most dangerous city for women by a 2017 thomson reuters poll. egypt's government has put in place policies that restrict the women who are trying to speak up about harassment. laws granting government full control over social and traditional media allows the government to restrict free speech and silence women. ‚Äúbut the challenge we are facing now is to not allow them to politicize the case and drag it away from the sexual harassment issues

column2: but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

column1: in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23
column2: flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia
column3: and kushner spoke with kim darroch
column4: the british ambassador to the united states
column5: according to diplomats familiar with the conversations
column6: who spoke on condition of anonymity.

column1: the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump
column2: who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric
column3: took office on jan. 20. it failed
column4: with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

column1: the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move
column2: egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution
column3: prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

column1: a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a ""high level"" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.
according to court documents made public on friday
column2: a member of trump's presidential transition team
column3: later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner
column4: told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments
column6: to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

column2: cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan
column4: who told facebook he was conducting academic research
column5: built a facebook personality quiz app called ""thisisyourdigitalife."" when users downloaded the app
column6: it scraped all of their available facebook data
column8: their likes and where they lived.

column1: more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app
column2: which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download
column3: kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

column2: the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called ""psychographic targeting
column3: which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire
column4: where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm
